HEADWORD: Wort
<hw>Wort</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wort</ets>,
<ets>wurt</ets>, AS. <ets>wyrt</ets> herb, root; akin to OS.
<ets>wurt</ets>, G. <ets>wurz</ets>, Icel. <ets>jurt</ets>,
<ets>urt</ets>, Dan. <ets>urt</ets>, Sw. <ets>⟦oum⟧rt</ets>, Goth.
<ets>wa⟦uacute⟧rts</ets> a root, L. <ets>radix</ets>, Gr. <?/ a root,
<?/ a branch, young shoot, <?/ a branch, and E. <ets>root</ets>, n. Cf.
<er>Licorice</er>, <er>Orchard</er>, <er>Radish</er>, <er>Root</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, <er>Whortleberry</er>, <er>Wort</er> an infusion of
malt.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is now chiefly used in combination, as in
cole<xex>wort</xex>, fig<xex>wort</xex>, St. John's-<xex>wort</xex>,
wound<xex>wort</xex>, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Cabbages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wort
<hw>Wort</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>worte</ets>,
<ets>wurte</ets>, AS. <ets>wyrte</ets>; akin to OD. <ets>wort</ets>, G.
<ets>w⟦uum⟧rze</ets>, bier<ets>w⟦uum⟧rze</ets>, Icel. <ets>virtr</ets>,
Sw. <ets>v⟦oum⟧rt</ets>. See <er>Wort</er> an herb.]</ety> <def>An
infusion of malt which is unfermented, or is in the act of fermentation;
the sweet infusion of malt, which ferments and forms beer; hence, any
similar liquid in a state of incipient fermentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Wort</xex> consists essentially of a dilute
solution of sugar, which by fermentation produces alcohol and carbon
dioxide.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worth</ent>⟦br⟧
